
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `ico` (agar asl bashad), معمولا baraye tabdil dadan ya dastkari kardan file-haye `ICO` (Icon File Format) estefade mishavad. Amma, `ico` be عنوان yek dastoor standart dar Linux ya Unix mojood nist.  Dar natije, shoma ehtiaj darid yek barnameye khassi ke `ico` ra support mikonad نصب konid, ya az barname-haye dige mesle `ImageMagick` estefade konid ke mitavanad file-haye `ICO` ra dastkari konad. Be طور کلی, karhaee ke ba `ico` anjam mishavad shamel tabdil file-haye tasviri be format `ICO`, tagheer size, ya ویرایش icon-ha hast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha (با فرضیه اینکه یک برنامه ico نصب شده باشد):**
    🔹 `ico -convert input.png output.ico` --> 🖼️ Tabdil yek tasvir PNG be file ICO.
    🔹 `ico -resize 32x32 input.ico output.ico` --> 📐 Tagheer size icon be ابعاد 32x32 pixels.
    🔹 `ico -extract input.ico output.png` --> 📤 استخراج yek tasvir az file ICO be format PNG.

🛠 **Mesal-ha (با استفاده از ImageMagick):**

    $ convert input.png favicon.ico

    🔹 Tabdil tasvir `input.png` be `favicon.ico` با استفاده از دستور `convert` аз ImageMagick.

    $ identify favicon.ico

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at dar مورد file `favicon.ico` (mesle ab'ad va type).

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ convert logo.png icon.ico

    🔹  File tasvir `logo.png` be file icon `icon.ico` tabdil mishavad. Agar `logo.png` size مناسب نداشته باشد, ImageMagick به طور خودکار آنرا resize میکند.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `ico` command (if it exists) is typically used for converting or manipulating `ICO` (Icon File Format) files. However, `ico` is not a standard command in Linux or Unix systems. Therefore, you need to install a specific program that supports `ico`, or use other programs like `ImageMagick` that can manipulate `ICO` files. Common tasks performed with `ico` include converting image files to the `ICO` format, resizing, or editing icons.

⚙️ **Options (Assuming an ico program is installed):**
    🔹 `ico -convert input.png output.ico` --> 🖼️ Convert a PNG image to an ICO file.
    🔹 `ico -resize 32x32 input.ico output.ico` --> 📐 Resize the icon to 32x32 pixels.
    🔹 `ico -extract input.ico output.png` --> 📤 Extract an image from an ICO file to PNG format.

🛠 **Examples (Using ImageMagick):**

    $ convert input.png favicon.ico

    🔹 Converts the image `input.png` to `favicon.ico` using the `convert` command from ImageMagick.

    $ identify favicon.ico

    🔹 Displays information about the `favicon.ico` file (such as dimensions and type).

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ convert logo.png icon.ico

    🔹 The image file `logo.png` is converted into an icon file `icon.ico`. If `logo.png` doesn't have an appropriate size, ImageMagick will automatically resize it.

